#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:14
msgid "If you wanna run TestNG tests relying on @Parameters like the one below from Eclipse, you need to pass some value for the 'basedir' parameter, otherwise Eclipse will complain:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@Test(groups = \"unit\", enabled = true, testName = \"loaders.bdbje.BdbjeCacheStoreIntegrationTest\")\n"
"public class BdbjeCacheStoreIntegrationTest extends BaseCacheStoreTest {\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "  private String tmpDirectory;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  @BeforeTest\n"
"  @Parameters({\"basedir\"})\n"
"  protected void setUpTempDir(String basedir) {\n"
"     tmpDirectory = basedir + TestingUtil.TEST_PATH + File.separator + getClass().getSimpleName();\n"
"  }\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:42
msgid "Having looked around on the web, it's not clear how to do this and some people even seem to claim that http://markmail.org/message/n2gh4tjzzg5vozxy[it's not doable]. However, having looked at http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/testng.html[how Maven deals with this], you simply have to pass the parameter as system property and it will work. So, if you wanna run BdbjeCacheStoreIntegrationTest from Eclipse, simply pass a system property like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "-Dbasedir=/home/galder/tmp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:50
msgid "Otherwise, Eclipse will moan with a message like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2009-06-18-executing-testng-tests-relying-on.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"org.testng.TestNGException:\n"
"Parameter 'basedir' is required by @Configuration on method setUpTempDir\n"
msgstr ""
